by IceCream » Tue 11.10.2009 11:13 pm arggh sorry, i meant, "the present king of france is bald".It's:∃x - there exists an x such thatKx & ∀y - x is a king of France, and for all y,Ky → y=x - if y is a king of France then y=x& Bx - And, x is baldthere's a bit on it in the stanford encyclopedia, http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/russell/#RWAP and http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/logical-atomism/#2.3：）
